text: LaBarque Creek is an unincorporated community and census-designated place (CDP) in Jefferson County, Missouri, United States. Its population was 1,558 as of the 2010 census. ==Geography== The community is in northwestern Jefferson County and is named for LaBarque Creek, a tributary of the Meramec River. It is located on Missouri Route F, approximately northwest of Byrnesville on Big River,Pacific, Missouri, 7.5 Minute Topographic Quadrangle, USGS, 1954 (1984 rev.) southwest of Eureka on Interstate 44, and southwest of downtown St. Louis.
